47
00:02:15,456 --> 00:02:19,590
to encourage the development of renewable energy sources.

48
00:02:19,590 --> 00:02:21,230
And they did it in a very clever way.

49
00:02:21,230 --> 00:02:26,641
The feed-in tariff could be changed every year for any particular energy

50
00:02:26,641 --> 00:02:27,140
source.

51
00:02:27,140 --> 00:02:31,990
So, for example, if you wanted to put solar cells on your roof,

52
00:02:31,990 --> 00:02:34,680
you would get a guarantee of a particular price

53
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:38,210
for 30 years for the electricity produced from your solar cells.

54
00:02:38,210 --> 00:02:40,520
Now, if you put these solar cells up next year,

55
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:42,936
that price could be different because the government could

56
00:02:42,936 --> 00:02:45,490
change the feed-in tariff price every year.

57
00:02:45,490 --> 00:02:48,900
And the feed-in tariff for wind-- offshore, onshore--

58
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:51,990
would be different from solar and so on and so forth.

59
00:02:51,990 --> 00:02:54,650
So this is a way in which the government could actually

60
00:02:54,650 --> 00:02:59,370
provide incentives that developed the energy alternatives that

61
00:02:59,370 --> 00:03:03,490
were carbon free, essentially, in this particular way

62
00:03:03,490 --> 00:03:08,090
and could actually guide it along the way as they did it.

63
00:03:08,090 --> 00:03:10,030
Now, what did that do?

64
00:03:10,030 --> 00:03:14,770
It led to the fact that Germany still has the world's largest

65
00:03:14,770 --> 00:03:17,500
investment in photovoltaic devices.

66
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:20,645
It also developed wind in a very significant way.

67
00:03:20,645 --> 00:03:22,270
But it has to be done in the right way.

68
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:25,394
Spain, for example, did the same kind of thing-- this feed-in tariff thing.

69
00:03:25,394 --> 00:03:31,050
But in the case of Spain, they failed to ensure that the price of this

70
00:03:31,050 --> 00:03:33,990
was going to be passed on to the consumer.

71
00:03:33,990 --> 00:03:37,650
In Germany, the price was automatically passed on to the consumer.

72
00:03:37,650 --> 00:03:41,830
Now, the feed-in tariff concept is what's actually working in California

73
00:03:41,830 --> 00:03:45,820
and in Massachusetts in terms of utilities

74
00:03:45,820 --> 00:03:49,750
having a requirement to provide a certain amount of electricity that

75
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:51,930
comes from renewable sources.

76
00:03:51,930 --> 00:03:57,830
So we just put solar cells on our roof of our house in Cape Cod.

77
00:03:57,830 --> 00:04:00,860
Solar cells were put on the roof of the house in Cape Cod

78
00:04:00,860 --> 00:04:03,830
